    urllib.request.urlretrieve(data_source, zipname) #   python3.x

    #

        pass
    else:

    # pltfigaxfigure axesfigureaxarray

    ax.spines['right'].set_color('none')
    # x_datay_datascoloralpha
    ax.scatter(x_data, y_data, s = 10, color = '#539caf', alpha = 0.75)

    # 
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)

# 
def lineplotCI(x_data, y_data, sorted_x, low_CI, upper_CI, x_label, y_label, title):
    # 
    _, ax = plt.subplots()

    # 
    ax.plot(x_data, y_data, lw = 1, color = '#539caf', alpha = 1, label = 'Fit')
    # 
    ax.fill_between(sorted_x, low_CI, upper_CI, color = '#539caf', alpha = 0.4, label = '95% CI')
    # 
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)

    # labelloc=best
    ax.legend(loc = 'best')
    return ax

def lineplot2y(x_data, x_label, 
               y1_data, y1_color, y1_label, 
               y2_data, y2_color, y2_label, title):
    _, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.plot(x_data, y1_data, color = y1_color)
    # 
    ax1.set_ylabel(y1_label, color = y1_color)
    ax1.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax1.set_title(title)

    ax2 = ax1.twinx() # 
    ax2.plot(x_data, y2_data, color = y2_color)
    ax2.set_ylabel(y2_label, color = y2_color)
    # 
    ax2.spines['right'].set_visible(True)

def histogram(data, x_label, y_label, title, bins=10):
    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    res = ax.hist(data, color = '#539caf', bins=bins) # bin
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)
    return res

In[50]:
def overlaid_histogram(data1, data1_name, data1_color,
                       data2, data2_name, data2_color,
                       x_label, y_label, title):
    # bins
    max_nbins = 10
    data_range = [min(min(data1), min(data2)), max(max(data1), max(data2))]
    binwidth = (data_range[1] - data_range[0]) / max_nbins
    bins = np.arange(data_range[0], data_range[1] + binwidth, binwidth) # bins
    
    # Create the plot
    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data1, bins = bins, color = data1_color, alpha = 1, label = data1_name)
    ax.hist(data2, bins = bins, color = data2_color, alpha = 0.75, label = data2_name)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.legend(loc = 'best')

KDE: kernal density estimate

$$\hat{f}_h(x)=\frac{1}{n}\sum^n_{i=1}K_h(xx_i)=\frac{1}{nh}\sum^n_{i=1}K(\frac{xx_i}{h})$$

def barplot(x_data, y_data, error_data, x_label, y_label, title):
    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    # x_datastrfloat
    ax.bar(x_data, y_data, color = '#539caf', align = 'center')
    # 
    # ls='none'bar
    ax.errorbar(x_data, y_data, yerr = error_data, color = '#297083', ls = 'none', lw = 5) # lw
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)

def stackedbarplot(x_data, y_data_list, y_data_names, colors, x_label, y_label, title):
    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    # 
    for i in range(0, len(y_data_list)):
        if i == 0:
            ax.bar(x_data, y_data_list[i], color = colors[i], align = 'center', label = y_data_names[i])
        else:
            # 
            # 1bottom
            ax.bar(x_data, y_data_list[i], color = colors[i], bottom = y_data_list[i - 1], align = 'center', label = y_data_names[i])
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.legend(loc = 'upper right') #

def groupedbarplot(x_data, y_data_list, y_data_names, colors, x_label, y_label, title):
    _, ax = plt.subplots()
    # 
    total_width = 0.8
    # 
    ind_width = total_width / len(y_data_list)
    # 
    alteration = np.arange(-total_width/2+ind_width/2, total_width/2+ind_width/2, ind_width)

    # 
    for i in range(0, len(y_data_list)):
        # 
        ax.bar(x_data + alteration[i], y_data_list[i], color = colors[i], label = y_data_names[i], width = ind_width)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.legend(loc = 'upper right')

def boxplot(x_data, y_data, base_color, median_color, x_label, y_label, title):
    _, ax = plt.subplots()

    # 
    ax.boxplot(y_data
               # 
               , patch_artist = True
               # 
               , medianprops = {'color': base_color}
               # colorfacecolor
               , boxprops = {'color': base_color, 'facecolor': median_color}
               # whisker
               , whiskerprops = {'color': median_color}
               # whisker cap
               , capprops = {'color': base_color})

    # x_data
    ax.set_xticklabels(x_data)
    ax.set_ylabel(y_label)
    ax.set_xlabel(x_label)
    ax.set_title(title)
